  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective was to assess adverse event risk in the use of Nitrous Oxide for Pediatric
      Dental Patients. The investigators performed a multicenter observational study. The
      investigators included patients aged 1 to 18 years and who have already failed dental care
      because of non-cooperation; they could be with mental or cognitive disabilities and could
      have sedative premedication. The investigators performed any type of dental care With the Use
      of Nitrous Oxide/Oxygen Sedation. The primary outcome was vomiting assessed during or after
      dental care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
